- Mestre Zé Maria (José Maria da Silva, 1948-2016) - trained 1966 in Tijuca, Rio de Janeiro

"PULO DO GATO" TECHNIQUE:
Both Paulinho Salmon and Euclides Paes are credited with teaching this "famous secret" technique to Zé Maria. The nature of the technique is not described in available sources, but the name ("Cat''s Leap") suggests acrobatic agility.

GRUPO CAPOEIRA DA GUANABARA:
Both Salmon and Euclides Paes were associated with this group. Zé Maria graduated as instructor there in 1967. The group''s documentation is sparse; it appears distinct from the later Capoeira Guanabara founded in 1998.

IPHAN COMMITTEE:
Member of a committee of Rio de Janeiro capoeira mestres that consults with IPHAN on safeguarding measures. Active as of 2014.

